ZH: 他的无知导致了许多错误。
EN: His ignorance led to many mistakes.

ZH: 她是个无知的人，对这个话题一无所知。
EN: She is ignorant and knows nothing about this topic.

ZH: 无知是罪恶的根源。
EN: Ignorance is the root of evil.

ZH: 孩子们的无知令人忧虑。
EN: The ignorance of children is worrying.

ZH: 我们应该努力消除无知。
EN: We should strive to eliminate ignorance.

ZH: 他太无知以至于自认为无所不能。
EN: He is so ignorant that he thinks he can do anything.

ZH: 这些误解都来自无知。
EN: These misunderstandings all stem from ignorance.

ZH: 教育可以帮助消除无知。
EN: Education can help eradicate ignorance.

ZH: 他因无知而犯下了错误。
EN: He made mistakes due to his ignorance.

ZH: 她的无知让她感到无助。
EN: Her ignorance makes her feel helpless.

ZH: 社会中存在许多种类的无知。
EN: There are many forms of ignorance in society.

ZH: 无知导致了许多冲突。
EN: Ignorance leads to many conflicts.

ZH: 无知会让人变得愚蠢。
EN: Ignorance can make people foolish.

ZH: 没有教育只会导致更多的无知。
EN: Lack of education only leads to more ignorance.

ZH: 无知是心灵的枷锁。
EN: Ignorance is the shackles of the mind.

ZH: 无知使人盲目。
EN: Ignorance makes people blind.

ZH: 无知是人类最大的敌人。
EN: Ignorance is humanity's greatest enemy.

ZH: 她因无知而失去了机会。
EN: She lost opportunities due to her ignorance.

ZH: 无知的人常常被人误导。
EN: Ignorant people are often misled.

ZH: 当你接受自己的无知，你才能成长。
EN: Growth comes when you accept your ignorance.
